Russian President Vladimir Putin signed the Law on the introduction of administrative liability for violation of the time and order of payment of goods (works, services) in the execution of procurement for state and municipal needs.
The law is designed to solve the very serious problem of failing to comply with its obligations by customers in the execution of public and municipal purchases.
Another two years ago, the situation in which entrepreneurs could not receive payment for already executed state and municipal contracts was widespread.
At that time, the President of Russia instructed the Prosecutor General of the Russian Federation to take the issue of special control.
Because the businessmen themselves could not cope with unscrupulous customers who were not supported by the Financing of the contracts, they tried to evade the payment obligations and included illegal conditions in the contracts.
The problem was systemic in the country.
Since 2015, in the interests of protecting the rights of entrepreneurs to receive payment on public orders, the Prosecutor's Office has made 9.7 thousand submissions, according to the results of their consideration of disciplinary measures involving 4.5 thousand officials, to administrative - 533, to the investigative bodies for the organization of legal proceedings, 75 materials have been filed, 46 of them have been initiated criminal cases.
As a result, the debt to entrepreneurs in the amount of more than 66 billion roubles was paid.
And these huge amounts have accumulated far beyond the non-payment of multi-billion contracts.
There have been numerous, systematic delays in the payment of services to entrepreneurs on the far more modest amounts.
Here is a typical case.
The head of the small Company won a competition for the provision of social services services for several million rubles.
The person invested all of his revolving funds, fully fulfilled the obligations, but the money was not received on time.
The result is an increasing financial balance of wages, taxes, loans that would lead to bankruptcy if the entrepreneur did not ask for assistance from the Prosecutor's Office.
Now, in a number of regions, the problem has managed to maximize the problem.
However, as of the first half of 2017, the total amount of debt on state and municipal contracts, identified by prosecutors of the subjects of the Russian Federation, amounted to about 27.4 billion roubles.
In regions where debt indicators continue to reach critical values, the Public Prosecutor's Office operates in a manual crisis management regime.
The Attorney General is personally conducting visiting meetings with representatives of the local authorities, where all public prosecutors have dealt with violations and measures to remove them immediately.
Such operational meetings have already been held in Yaroslavl and Yekaterinburg this year.
Qualitatively improving the payment discipline of public customers will be able to implement Federal Law No. 189-FZ "On Amendments to the Code of the Russian Federation on Administrative Offences in order to establish administrative liability of officials of the client for the violation of the period and order of payment of goods (works, services) in the implementation of the procurement for the provision of state and municipal needs," which was signed last week by the President of Russia.
The draft law was drafted by the Ministry of Economic Development of Russia on the initiative of the Prosecutor General.
The new law will supplement the Code of the Russian Federation on Administrative Offences, which provides for a fine of 30 thousand to 50 thousand rubles for the violation of the term and order of payment of goods, works and services in public and municipal procurement.
And if an official has already been subjected to administrative punishment for a similar offence, he is awaiting disqualification for a period of between one and two years.
All prosecutors of the constituent entities of the Russian Federation have already been instructed to ensure the application of these legislation in practice.
