For walking around the city in a swimsuit or with a naked cake, there will now be a penalty of 200 euros.
For 100 euros, it will require those who organize a picnic in a public place or ride a bike on pedestrian areas, TASS reports to the Association of Tour Operators of Russia.
Moreover, it is mentioned that the authorities provide for a fine for the inscriptions on monuments 400 euros and for rubbish 25 euros.
To inform tourists about the need to comply with the rules of behaviour in Venice will be with the help of a special company "enjoy, respect Venice" (# enjoyment) on social media, as well as through advertisements and posters on the website of the City Council, on billboards and in places where tourists are most likely.
The campaign will be conducted in 10 languages.
According to the tourism adviser of Venice, Paola Mar, information about fines will be transferred to the embassies of the relatives of the offenders, so as to warn their compatriots from such mistakes.
"The problem is that Venice is perceived as a beach," she said.
In April, the administration of the Italian city announced plans to limit the tour.
In Venice, a restriction on the number of tourists visiting the city centre has already been successfully implemented.
Instead of 100,000 people who wish to observe the Festa del redentory Festival, only 60,000 guests were admitted to the scene.
In addition, a moratorium on the creation of new hotels and fast food restaurants in the historic part of Venice has been introduced.
