Electricity is cheap for residents and for producers of Buryatia
The efforts of the Soviet and post-Soviet authorities of the Republic of Buryatia (Eastern Siberia) to establish fair tariffs for consumers of electric energy are beginning to bear fruit.
As of September 1, 25% of the electricity costs are low for industrial consignees.
The Federal Antimonopoly Service of the country, in accordance with the decision of the Government of the Russian Federation "On Amendments to the rules of the wholesale electricity and power market and in the consolidated forecast balance of the production and supply of electrical energy (power) within the framework of the Unified Energy System of Russia on subjects of the Russian Federation" (dated 17.07.2017 No. 842), established indicative prices for electricity and power for industrial consumers of the Republic of Buryatia.
As a result, the cost of electric power for Buryat producers is reduced by a quarter, which will significantly facilitate the lives of small and medium-sized enterprises and individual entrepreneurs.
For many decades, the leaders of the Republic have offended the vices of Moscow offices in their futile efforts to equate the region in tariffs with the neighboring Irkutsk region with a cascade of hydroelectric power plants in the hangar, flowing from Baikal, the main watershed of which is Buryatia.
And only this year the movement began.
In March, electricity tariffs for the population of the Republic were reduced from 4.24 roubles/kWh to 3.93 roubles/kWh, or 7.3%.
With the inclusion of Buryatia by a decision of the Federal Government on the list of Territories of the wholesale market, for which the peculiarities of the operation of wholesale and retail markets have been established, the industrial consumers' skull has been established.
According to analysts, this is only the beginning, as the population of the Irkutsk region pays for kilowatt/hour 1.01 roubles.
But no one is going to call at least the approximate date of new tariff shifts towards Buryatia.
