Ukraine proposed to send Russians to prison for illegal border crossing
In the Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine, a draft law is registered, according to which the Republic may have criminal punishment for Russians for the illegal crossing of the Ukrainian border.
According to the RT TV channel, registered in the electronic database of the Ukrainian Parliament, the document suggests three years imprisonment for Russian citizens trying to get illegally into the territory of the country.
It is noted that for a repeat offence or an act committed by a group of persons, the term of imprisonment may be increased to five years.
If the perpetrator was detained on the border with weapons, the time of detention for him will rise to eight years.
Previously, it was reported that Ukrainian border guards detained Ukrainians who tried to enter Russia outside the established checkpoints.
