In Russia there will be two new territories ahead of social and economic development - "Abaza" and "Novotroitsk."
The relevant decisions of the Government of the Russian Federation will come into force today, August 4.
The boundaries and types of economic activity of the Torah are defined in the territory of the city of Abaza in the Republic of Khakassia.
In the city where 15 thousand people live, there will be a special legal regime for business activity, as well as the minimum capital investment of residents, the minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is expected that this will attract about 2.5 billion roubles in the city, and more than 600 new jobs will be created.
The list of economic activities in which the "abase" Tor will operate a special legal regime for business activities, for example, includes crop production, animal husbandry, food production, non-alcoholic beverages and clothing.
Already, the Government of the Republic has signed framework agreements on the implementation of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependence of the Territory on the town forming enterprise of "Abakan mine."
In January 2017, the authorities of the region reported that Khakassia fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of Economic Development for the creation of a Tor.
Similarly, the authorities of the Orenburg region have also received.
There, in the city of Novotroitsk, the Territory will also be created in advance of social and economic development.
This will allow to diversify the economy of the monotowns, to reduce its dependence on the town forming enterprise of JSC "Ural Steel," as well as to create more than 2.3 thousand jobs and to attract investments in the amount of more than 8 billion roubles.
The list of economic activities in which the new ToR will operate a special legal regime for entrepreneurs include, among other things, freshwater fish farming, the production of feed, medicines and medical materials.
Novotroitsk became the first of the mono-cities of the Orenburg Region, who received the status of Tor.
Let us recall that the territory of advance development is an economic zone with preferential tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges, which are created to attract investment and improve the lives of the population.
Among the benefits for resident residents are the following: a profit tax of not more than 5% for the first five years, and at least 10% over the next five years, social contributions of 7.6% for 10 years, the use of a free customs zone regime, a preferential treatment regime for various infrastructure facilities, as well as preferential rates for rent.
